s a fortune  operator of highend department stores in the united states under the nameplate saks fifth avenue it was founded in birmingham alabama and is currently headquartered in new york city contents  history  proffitts inc  saks inc  divestments  former department store group  acquisition by hbc  restatements  see also  notes  external links historyedit proffitts incedit proffitts inc began as five proffitts stores in the knoxville tennessee metropolitan area after going public under the symbol prft on the nasdaq stock exchange in  proffitts inc grew by acquiring several department stores in  the company purchased  hesss locations in tennessee virginia kentucky and georgia from  to  the company added mcraes younkers parisian herbergers carson pirie scott boston store and bergners chains as well as additional stores from lovemans parksbelk and brodys which were converted into existing store nameplates after acquiring parisian proffitts relocated its corporate headquarters to birmingham alabama from knoxville in october  although the full saks company no longer has a store in mississippi saks operates its data services from the former mcraes headquarters in jackson mississippi saks incedit in september  the company acquired the holding company for the luxury retailer saks fifth avenue saks holdings inc and subsequently changed its legal name to saks incorporated the acquisition brought the saks fifth avenue and off th franchises as well as folio a mailorder business and sakscom an online retailer the former saks fifth avenue properties became the saks fifth avenue enterprises division of the company with the larger birminghambased department store division becoming the saks department store group the companys mainline department store group was made up of its southern department store group mcraes and proffittsthe northern department store group bergners boston store carson pirie scott herbergers and younkers the companys specialty department store group parisian and the companys saks fifth avenue enterprises which included saks fifth avenue and off th in  the company recorded record revenues of  billion making it a member of the fortune  and one of the largest operators of department stores in the united states the company was also a primary sponsor of the brunos memorial classic golf tournament now known as the regions charity classic the company moved its headquarters to midtown manhattan new york city in  several of saks management still live in birmingham in  vendors filed against saks alleging unlawful chargebacks the us securities and exchange commission sec investigated the complaint for years and according to the new york times exposed a tangle of illicit tactics that let saks  keep money it owed to clothing makers inflating saks yearly earnings up to  and abusively collecting around  million from suppliers over seven years saks settled with the sec in  after firing three or more executives involved in the fraudulent activities divestmentsedit by  saks incorporated began to seek a narrower focus towards the luxuryoriented retail synonymous with its saks fifth avenue stores the decision resulted in a july  sale of its combined  proffitts and mcraes stores to belk for approximately  million on october  that same year saks announced that it was selling the  stores within its northern department store group including carson pirie scott bergners younkers herbergers and boston store to bonton stores inc for  billion the transaction was complete as of march   on august   saks incorporated announced that it had agreed to sell its upscale  parisian stores along with two regional distribution centers and birmingham corporate headquarters to belk which rebranded them under their own name in the third quarter of  on november   saks announced the closure of the unprofitable club libby lu chain in late august  the uk tabloid daily mail reported that a private equity buyer was mulling a  billion takeover bid for saks incorporated